The [[Planet/Legends|planet]]<ref name="TEA">''[[The Essential Atlas]]''</ref> [[Tothis]] had a nightclub called the '''Green Planet''',<ref name="SWI 67" /> which was also a [[Cantina/Legends|cantina]].<ref name="DB">{{DB|character|greeata|Jendowanian, Greeata}}</ref> The [[Musician/Legends|musicians]] [[Sy Snootles/Legends|Sy Snootles]] and [[Greeata Jendowanian/Legends|Greeata Jendowanian]] worked there for a [[Time/Legends|time]]<ref name="CSWE" /> and were the only employees not addicted to [[Spice/Legends|spice]].<ref name="SWI 67" /> In the final [[Standard year/Legends|years]] of the [[Clone Wars/Legends|Clone Wars]],<ref name="Part 2">{{SW|url=news/slugthrowers-part-2|series=Slugthrowers: An Overview of Popular Music and Musicians in a Galaxy Far, Far Away|text=Part 2|nolive=1}}</ref> a conflict that lasted from [[22 BBY/Legends|22]] to [[19 BBY/Legends|19 BBY]],<ref name="NEC">''[[The New Essential Chronology]]''</ref> musician [[Evar Orbus/Legends|Evar Orbus]] visited the Green Planet while looking for members to join his [[Evar Orbus and His Galactic Jizz-Wailers|band]], ultimately hiring both Jendowanian and Snootles<ref name="SWI 67" /> after Orbus's bandmate [[Max Rebo/Legends|Max Rebo]] noticed the pair and was taken in by Snootles' singing.<ref name="SETSB">''[[Star Wars Trilogy Sourcebook, Special Edition]]''</ref>

==Behind the scenes==
The Green Planet was first indirectly mentioned in [[1997]]'s ''[[Star Wars Trilogy Sourcebook, Special Edition]]'', a supplement for [[West End Games]]' ''[[Star Wars: The Roleplaying Game]]''.<ref name="SETSB" /> The cantina was first named in "[[Who's Who in the Max Rebo Band]]," an article [[Rich Handley]] wrote for the [[Star Wars Insider 67|sixty-seventh issue]] of the ''[[Star Wars Insider]]'' magazine,<ref name="SWI 67" /> which was published on [[April 15]], [[2003]].<ref name="SW.com">{{SWArchive|url=community/news/2003/03/news20030317.html|text=Celebrate <i>Jedi</i>'s 20th in ''Insider'' #67}}</ref>

